&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission at Sourcegraph is to make it so that &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Mission-values-e9d37e6b972a4ef395c3076aea2bd07d?pvs=4&quot;&gt;everyone can code&lt;/a&gt;, not just ~0.1% of the population.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are transforming how the world‚Äôs most important companies build software by industrializing development with AI. Today, most professional developers spend a disproportionate amount of time understanding code and performing repetitive, low-level tasks‚Äîleaving less time for innovation and meaningful impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We‚Äôre changing that. Sourcegraph brings AI-powered search and agents to the enterprise, helping teams automate the mundane and amplify what developers do best‚Äî solving hard problems and creating great products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here‚Äôs how we‚Äôre making a difference:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accelerating developers &lt;/strong&gt;with AI agents that deliver insights and precision‚Äîenabling 5x faster test creation, 30% increase in merge requests, and saving 20 minutes per developer daily.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automating repetitive tasks,&lt;/strong&gt; from remediating vulnerabilities (saving teams 1,000+ hours annually) to speeding up migrations that would take years to months.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enabling innovation&lt;/strong&gt; by addressing complex problems like automated bug triage, vulnerability detection, and AI-driven code reviews seamlessly integrated into workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trusted by 7/10 top software companies by market cap, 4/6 top US banks and many of the companies leading global innovation, like Stripe, Indeed, Tesla, and 1Password, and with $225M in funding from investors like &lt;a href=&quot;https://techcrunch.com/2021/07/13/sourcegraph-raises-125m-series-d-on-2-6b-valuation-for-universal-code-search-tool/&quot;&gt;a16z&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://about.sourcegraph.com/blog/series-c-with-sequoia/&quot;&gt;Sequoia&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.redpoint.com/companies/sourcegraph/&quot;&gt;Redpoint&lt;/a&gt;, we are building the tools that will define the next era of enterprise software development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you‚Äôre passionate about solving the hardest problems in software and shaping the future of technology, join us. Let‚Äôs build something extraordinary together.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours &amp;amp; location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üåé While we hire &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/How-we-engage-talent-outside-of-the-US-218f7193695a46cbb1ef39ef9c1f72d4&quot;&gt;almost anywhere&lt;/a&gt; in the world, we have a preference for someone to reside in the San Francisco Bay Area for this role for proximity to our partners and the people you will work with the most. In San Francisco, we would ask that you work from our San Francisco office at least three days per week. &amp;nbsp;However, if you feel qualified, we welcome you to apply regardless of location. No matter what, working hours must overlap with the Pacific time zone for at least 30 hours/week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that flexibility is required to accommodate partners located in different time zones around the world. &amp;nbsp;Moderate travel is required for both internal (Sourcegraph facing) and external (partner facing) meetings and conferences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;San Francisco, CA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We do not subscribe to ‚ÄúI do my best work when I work 40 hours a week.‚Äù &amp;nbsp;People we hire at Sourcegraph believe that building outstanding things means working very hard ‚Äî smarter and more hours than the competition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this job is exciting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Partner Solution Engineer (pre-sales), you will play a key role in developing Sourcegraph‚Äôs partner ecosystem. &amp;nbsp;Partners are key to help extend Sourcegraph‚Äôs brand, to source new opportunities, to support the closing of business, and to drive customer success. &amp;nbsp;This is a broadly cross functional role, which requires interactions with a variety of different stakeholders within Sourcegraph and our partners. &amp;nbsp;The ideal candidate will thrive working in a job with a wide variety of responsibilities and working with many different types of organizations and people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Partner Engineer will collaborate with the partner team to find, develop, activate, and manage these partnership relationships. &amp;nbsp;Additionally, the partner engineer will support our largest and most complex prospects and deployments, where there are sophisticated enterprise requirements which will exercise our product and novel ways which almost always leads to key organizational learnings and meaningful product updates. &amp;nbsp;The Partner Engineer will need to have strong intuition and judgment on how to best prioritize partners and activities within partner relationships. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with the following types of partnerships:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Channel partnerships - you will help to evangelize Sourcegraph in order to recruit relevant professional services and reseller firms worldwide, you will train, enable, and support these partners as they position Sourcegraph into their customers and support our implementations and customer deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software partnerships and technology alliances - you will help potential integration partners to understand Sourcegraph, will help to understand and coach them in building integrations (or build or help our engineering team to build integrations), will enable their teams to understand where and how to position to Sourcegraph, and will support the success of joint prospects and customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cloud partnerships - you will develop relationships with our key Cloud partners. &amp;nbsp;This includes staying current on their offerings and where we can collaborate with them, developing relationships with their key and relevant leaders, working through the technical aspects of their partner programs, and enabling their field teams. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÖ Within one month, you will‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about our products, our value propositions, our partners, our customers, our team, and our processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up your own fully configured sandbox instance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start building a trusting relationship with your peers on Sales, Value Engineering, Post-sales Success (Technical Advisory), Product, Engineering, and Support teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join customer and prospect calls with some of our largest customers to understand their needs, how we communicate the value of Sourcegraph, and how we deliver positive impact to our customers‚Äô business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get demo certified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get introduced to a set of key partners and join regular partner calls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ‚Äòfirst calls‚Äô with a partner to introduce them to Sourcegraph‚Äôs products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÖ Within three months, you will‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to take product and technical ownership of new and existing partner relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomously run both demo and training sessions for partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively address the majority of partner questions; develop internal relationships to answer others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a point of view on how different types of partners can uniquely leverage a Sourcegraph partnership (and product) to their benefit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for partners internally and externally. &amp;nbsp;Advocate to include partners in sales cycles and engagements. &amp;nbsp;Advocate for features that partners will find useful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and evolution of Sourcegraph‚Äôs partner program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to selected account teams managing large and sophisticated POC and customer relationships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìÖ Within six months, you will‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish yourself as a thought leader and evangelist by using your insights to teach partners and prospective partners new and better ways to get value from Sourcegraph&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor Sourcegraph teammates on how they can best leverage the partner ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join and contribute to teams managing large and sophisticated prospect and customer deployments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an enthusiastic, proactive, driven, and results-oriented Partner Solutions Engineer who shares&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.sourcegraph.com/company/values&quot;&gt; our values&lt;/a&gt; and has a passion for getting prospective customers to that a-ha moment with Sourcegraph and then helping them to build meaningful and mutually beneficial partnerships!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üîç The ideal candidate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 5 years experience in a relevant role such as Sales Engineering, Solutions Engineering, Professional Services, or Solution Architecture across a technical product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience selling Enterprise software solutions and have gone through the lived experience of the Enterprise process selling motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an innate curiosity of getting to the root of customer problems and understanding their motivations. You have a strong interest in how partners work together for the mutual benefit of each party - and for the customer!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You‚Äôre excited about the prospect of being directly involved in the advent of generative AI!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are well versed in back end infrastructure architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are very technically inclined and have a propensity to code and or hack code. You have experience writing code in one of the following (JavaScript, Python, Java, Go).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills, specifically across technical presentations and product demonstrations; ability to influence and excite a technical audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Either through direct experience or deep understanding, working knowledge of the end-to-end software development lifecycle and concepts such as continuous integration and continuous deployment. Note: You do not need to be a software engineer to be successful in this role!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy building tools, templates, and technical enablement collateral.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an organized approach to work, with demonstrated ability to proactively manage a set of concurrent relationships, to make difficult prioritization decisions, and to use data to guide decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You like diving in to learn a new skill to solve a problem that benefits or unblocks a partnership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You work well independently. &amp;nbsp;You can efficiently shift between demos and presentations, supporting partners, developing reusable assets, and jumping into sophisticated POC‚Äôs and / or deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìä This job is an IC3 position, depending on previous experience and role scope. You can read more about&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Leveling-Guide-0e1b5c76ada64b9caac387f8b7c4fc66&quot;&gt;our job leveling philosophy&lt;/a&gt; in our Handbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;üí∏ We pay you an above-average salary&lt;/strong&gt; because we want to hire the best people who are fully focused on helping Sourcegraph succeed, not worried about paying bills. As an &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Mission-values-e9d37e6b972a4ef395c3076aea2bd07d&quot;&gt;open and transparent&lt;/a&gt; company that values &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Compensation-Pay-Transparency-at-Sourcegraph-d58d0774f51b4b489d41c3628d30ff8d?pvs=4&quot;&gt;competitive compensation&lt;/a&gt;, our compensation ranges are visible to every single Sourcegraph teammate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your salary is determined by your pay band for the IC3 job level. For determining pay bands, we use a number of market and data-driven salary sources, along with your location zone, and target the high-end of the range to ensure we‚Äôre always paying above market regardless of where you live in the world. Both U.S. and international locations are divided into one of four zones, determined by the cost of labor index for each area. The salary for a successful candidate will be based on level, job-related skills, experience, qualifications, and location zone. Please note that the salaries below may be adjusted in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üí∞ The target compensation for this role is based on the IC3 pay band for your zone. The IC3 pay band for this role is&amp;nbsp;$150,000 USD base + $50,000 USD variable ($200,000 USD on-target-earnings).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìà In addition to our cash compensation, we offer equity (because when we succeed as a company, we want you to succeed, too) and generous &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Benefits-Perks-dd1da4b6b3a64780abed010a144d34ba&quot;&gt;perks &amp;amp; benefits&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Below is the interview process you can expect for this role (you can read more about &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Types-of-interviews-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;the types of interviews&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; in our Handbook). It may look like a lot of steps, but rest assured that we move quickly and the steps are designed to help you get the information needed to determine if we‚Äôre the right fit for you‚Ä¶ Interviewing is a two-way street, after all!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We expect the interview process to take 3.25 hours in total.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;üëã Introduction Stage&lt;/strong&gt; - we have initial conversations to get to know you better‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[30m]&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#99be5ff628b2414194a0ba79d9f25f13&quot;&gt;Recruiter Screen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[45m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#1919882c0cf147c487eb1df40db8a694&quot;&gt;Hiring Manager Screen&lt;/a&gt; /&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#c678a2a86e0e47e4958507e869bf7ded&quot;&gt;Resume Deep Dive&lt;/a&gt; with Hiring Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;üßë‚Äçüíª Team Interview Stage&lt;/strong&gt; - we then delve into your experience in more depth and introduce you to members of the team, including cross-functional partners‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[30m]&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#cb00697e95304550a146c32563c0255d&quot;&gt;Cross-functional&lt;/a&gt; /&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#88b9f826dee04ef98afc2aeec35b877a&quot;&gt;Peer&lt;/a&gt; with an Account Executive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[45m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Technical-Success-interview-process-902069565e1147b89ac98054179eb676?pvs=4#5a1021deb9b140258e35bbdd345f7754&quot;&gt;Live Panel Demo and Q&amp;amp;A&lt;/a&gt; with Hiring Manager, 1 Solutions Engineer &amp;amp; 1 AE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;üéâ Final Interview Stage &lt;/strong&gt;- we move you to our final round, where you gain a better understanding of our business and values holistically‚Ä¶&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[30m]&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/Types-of-interviews-sample-questions-f279f080583d49ee9f2c60e30c8cb1f7?pvs=4#e3a04291743048df87541a88aa8199dd&quot;&gt;Values&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;[15m] &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/sourcegraph/How-to-work-with-Quinn-Slack-CEO-807673e0864d473f959cc4efd9642a5a?pvs=4#6f185c0e2011411eac5be9c675f9056c&quot;&gt;Leadership&lt;/a&gt; with co-founder&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We check references and conduct your background check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note - you are welcome to request additional conversations with anyone you would like to meet, but didn‚Äôt get to meet during the interview process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(243, 78, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn more about us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can learn more about what it is like to work at Sourcegraph by reading &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/d7614e3e9dc04c09ac2d42d57f1816e6?v=2a6d426dbae14390b155120b0c029ce0&quot;&gt;our handbook&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an ambitious team who are collectively working hard to build the most influential company in the world.&amp;nbsp; You can read more about our &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/What-it-s-like-working-at-Sourcegraph-119a8e11265880b18911eee4d9b7c460#119a8e1126588062b935fc66104b6115&quot;&gt;culture&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Compensation-Pay-Transparency-at-Sourcegraph-d58d0774f51b4b489d41c3628d30ff8d?pvs=74&quot;&gt;competitive compensation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/Benefits-Perks-dd1da4b6b3a64780abed010a144d34ba?pvs=74&quot;&gt;benefits&lt;/a&gt; here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sourcegraph is an equal opportunity workplace; we welcome people from all backgrounds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sourcegraph participates in &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://sourcegraph.notion.site/E-Verify-2ab3286dde3446d6bac2898c83610107&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;E-Verify&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; for U.S. Employees. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OneLocal is looking to hire &lt;strong&gt;SEO freelancers &lt;/strong&gt;on a short-contract basis to assist with updating the website&#39;s SEO audit digital presence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You‚Äôll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct comprehensive on-page and technical SEO audits for our websites and provide actionable feedback to our internal team based on your findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct competitor analysis to identify content gaps and opportunities to improve or expand existing content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide reports and insights on each audit to our account management team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing optimizations to our Google Business Profiles (GBP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other tasks as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with content creation or copywriting focused on local SEO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of conversion rate optimization (CRO) and its relationship to SEO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Core Web Vitals, schema markup, and technical SEO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of local SEO tactics and strategies, including Content optimization and link-building strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and experience working within a development team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with industry-standard tools such as Screaming Frog, SEMRush, Ahrefs, or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with industry-standard tools such as Google Search Console, Google Analytics&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated with excellent time management, attention to detail, and a demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects effectively and efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of HTML&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Uberall&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in Jira&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will be paying at a rate of USD $5.50 per hour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: OneLocal pays freelancers using Direct Deposit. Please only apply for this position if you can get paid via Direct Deposit. Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented &lt;strong&gt;Freelance Content Writer&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong background in &lt;strong&gt;martech, CRM, or agency-related topics&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team. This role is ideal for a writer who can produce high-quality, in-depth blog posts and case studies while maintaining an authoritative, market analyst tone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create compelling, research-driven blog posts on marketing trends, CRM providers, SMB marketing strategies, product insights, and case studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write with an authoritative voice, demonstrating expertise and thought leadership in the industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our SEO freelancer to align on keywords and content strategies when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct independent research using internal resources and publicly available data (no technical interviews with subject matter experts required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce several pieces of content per week, ensuring quality, consistency, and timely delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Jira for task tracking (familiarity is helpful but not required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus solely on writing‚Äîour in-house designer handles graphic and multimedia content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in content writing, blogging, or journalism, particularly in martech, CRM, or digital marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to analyze industry trends and translate them into insightful, well-structured content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent research and analytical skills with a keen eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of SEO best practices and experience optimizing content for search.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to write in a clear, engaging, and authoritative style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional time management and organizational skills to meet deadlines consistently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing for SaaS, B2B, or marketing agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Jira or other project management tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in marketing technology, automation, and CRM ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an hourly, ongoing freelance role with no designated end date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rate:&lt;/strong&gt; USD 5.5 per hour&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; We process freelancer payments via &lt;strong&gt;Direct Deposit&lt;/strong&gt;. Please apply only if you can receive payments via this method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re a strategic thinker, a skilled storyteller, and passionate about marketing and CRM content, we&#39;d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
